This paper deals with the network spectral efficiency of decentralized vector multiple access channels (MACs), which involves information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also considers the use of successive interference cancelation (SIC), which falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SI). The optimization of data rates and the use of water-filling techniques are related to mathematical modeling (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the existence of an optimal number of dimensions, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT).
